Reminiscing the early days!! 

When people told me “dont do it”, I am Glad I didn’t listen to them or take their advice. 

6 years ago, i hardly had anything figured out. All I knew was the life I lived in India, the friends I had, the career I built, and the joy and excitement of just living life. 

To just up and leave everything behind was such a tough decision that even in those moments of doubt and fear, my gut told me to just go for it. With the hopes of building something new and the lack of confidence in myself, I closed my eyes and pictured a full life. One that not only would bring me happiness, but also a purpose. A life that would challenge me beyond my wildest dreams, but nonetheless a dream in the making.

Today, reflecting on how much I’ve worked non-stop just to get here and still do it to achieve all my dreams. 

If I listened to people who said “don’t do it”. I literally wouldn’t be who I am. I’m an entrepreneur, a wife, a mom, a daughter, a friend. There is so much more to achieve and this is just the beginning. 

Don’t be afraid to shine your light that others work so hard to DIM. Keep shining 🤍🫶
